╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 1: Impersonation
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attacker claims caller_id='fake-admin' with a fabricated signature.
  S must reject any caller_id not in caller_keys.json.

  Baseline (no S)        │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway (S)            │ HTTP 403 │ unknown_caller                   │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 2: Replay
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attacker captures a legitimately signed request and resends it verbatim.
  S must reject any request whose nonce has already been seen.

  Baseline 1st send      │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Baseline replay        │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway 1st send       │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway replay         │ HTTP 403 │ replay_nonce_reused              │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 3: Tampering
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attacker intercepts a signed request for the harmless file and
  rewrites the path argument to point at the secret file.
  S must detect the modification via signature verification.

  Baseline (tampered)    │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway (tampered)     │ HTTP 403 │ bad_signature                    │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 4: Session Hijacking
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Variant A — Bypass: call a tool with no s.init → s.ready handshake.
  Variant B — Forged proof: obtain a challenge then submit an invalid proof.

  Baseline (bypass)      │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway (bypass)       │ HTTP 403 │ missing_session_id               │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   
  Gateway (forged proof) │ HTTP 403 │ bad_ready_proof                  │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 5: Unauthorized Tool Access
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attacker calls read_file on the secret path.
  S must enforce TOOL_POLICIES: read_file is not in the allowlist.

  Baseline file content: "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
  Baseline (no ACL)      │ HTTP 200 │ 200 OK                           │ MCP2: YES — reached MCP2 │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway (ACL enforced) │ HTTP 403 │ tool_not_allowed                 │ MCP2: NO  — blocked at S │ ✓ BLOCKED   

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 6: MITM (Man-in-the-Middle)
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attacker runs a relay that intercepts HTTP traffic between MCP1 and MCP2.
  Without TLS, the relay has full read/write access to all messages.
  S with ENABLE_TLS=true encrypts the channel end-to-end.
  Full live demo: node tests/baseline_mitm.js + node tests/mitm_protected.js

  Baseline (HTTP)    │ HTTP 200 │ Proxy reads & rewrites plaintext   │ MCP2: YES — via proxy │ ✗ VULNERABLE
  Gateway (TLS)      │  —       │ TLS rejects connection from proxy  │ MCP2: NO              │ ✓ BLOCKED   

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  PERFORMANCE EVALUATION
  5 warmup + 50 timed requests per scenario  |  10 session establishments
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Scenario                         │  mean  │  p50   │  p95   │  p99   │   min  │   max  (ms)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (A) Baseline (no S)              │   0.42 │   0.40 │   0.55 │   0.65 │   0.36 │   0.65
  (B) Gateway (S) — session reused │   0.74 │   0.71 │   1.00 │   1.12 │   0.65 │   1.12
  (C) Session establishment        │   3.26 │   3.26 │   3.46 │   3.46 │   3.16 │   3.46

  Per-request gateway overhead: +0.32 ms mean  (+76.5% vs baseline)
  Session amortisation: if a session handles ≥10 requests, establishment cost
  (~3.3 ms) adds < 0.33 ms per request.

  Gateway resource usage during 50 defended requests:
    RSS memory  : 55.80 MB → 57.77 MB  (Δ 1.97 MB)
    Heap used   : 8.86 MB → 10.04 MB  (Δ 1.17 MB)
    CPU user    : +14.6 ms   CPU system: +2.4 ms

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  DEFENSE EVALUATION SUMMARY
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  #   Attack                       Baseline       Gateway (S)                            MCP2 reached?
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  1   Impersonation                ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (unknown_caller)             No
  2   Replay                       ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (replay_nonce_reused)        No
  3   Tampering                    ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (bad_signature)              No
  4   Session Hijacking            ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (missing_session_id)         No
  5   Unauthorized Tool Access     ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (tool_not_allowed)           No
  6   MITM                         ✗ VULNERABLE   ✓ BLOCKED (TLS encryption)             No

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Result: 6/6 attacks BLOCKED — S prevents all attacks from reaching MCP2.

  Defense layers and what they block:
    Layer 1 — Method allowlist      blocks: unknown-method abuse
    Layer 2 — TLS / mTLS            blocks: MITM, eavesdropping
    Layer 3 — Cryptographic auth    blocks: impersonation, tampering, replay
    Layer 4 — mTLS CN binding       blocks: cert/identity mismatch
    Layer 5 — Session + ACL         blocks: session hijacking, unauthorized access

  Performance overhead (50 requests each):
    Baseline mean latency : 0.42 ms
    Gateway mean latency  : 0.74 ms
    Absolute overhead     : +0.32 ms per request
    Relative overhead     : +76.5%
    Session setup cost    : 3.3 ms (amortised over N calls)
